                <h1>Ford History: A Legacy of Innovation</h1>
                <p>Ford, founded by Henry Ford in 1903, revolutionized the automobile industry with the introduction of assembly line production. The Model T, launched in 1908, made cars affordable for the masses. Over the decades, Ford expanded globally, innovating with features like safety technologies and electric vehicles, and making a significant impact on American culture and economy.</p>
